reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 27, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I recently got my hands on this dirt bike battery, and let me tell you, it's amazing! This battery is super reliable, giving me the power I need for my adventures on the trails. It's also built to last, so I don't have to worry about it failing me when I'm out in the middle of nowhere. Plus, the performance is top-notch, delivering consistent power and keeping my bike running smoothly. I highly recommend this battery!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 9, 2014
reviews.reviewText: It's a battery. It was advertised to come fully charged and I was blown away when it actually was! I mean it was FULLY charged. It went into a Baccio 50 cc scooter. When I hooked a charger|maintainer up to it first, the green light on the charger stayed on, which indicates COMPLETELY CHARGED! WOW! It turned over the scooter's motor at warp speed, when I tried that next! I'm still amazed. What did they do, leave it connected to a battery charger in the warehouse until I ordered it!?But here's where it gets even MORE amazing! It's at a really nice price with free shipping, rigtht? Been there, done that, right? It's going to take them several days to even ship it, right? Then it's going to come FedEx super saver or some nonsense, where they hand it over to the Post Office and it takes forever, right? WRONG!! WRONG and WRONG! They shipped it while I wasn't looking, so I can't even tell you, but it was a matter of hours! They shipped it USPS two day priority <FOR FREE>! It got here (over 1000 miles) as fast as if I'd paid $23 (or more!) for 2nd day shipping!! I've never had this happen! I CANNOT say enough good things about Chrome Battery.Maybe Amazon could consider outsourcing their warehouse and shipping department to these people!?There are no words for how completely satisfied I am with everything about this purchase. I only wish it was something like a Porsche instead of just a battery...

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 30, 2015
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars so I knew the old battery was fine, and as a bonus
reviews.reviewText: I purchased this battery as a "diagnostic test" to see if my KTM dirt bike had charging system problems. The electric starter was becoming very weak, and I suspected that maybe the old battery was A: weak, or B: not charging properly.Replacing the old battery with this one showed the same symptoms, so I knew the old battery was fine, and as a bonus, I now have a spare battery.Very well worth the $23 spent on this.Turns out that my starter was the problem.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Beware mod No Return Policy
reviews.reviewText: I take responsibility for not paying attention, I searched for lawn mower battery, and mistakenly order this little guy. This was so small it was delivered in a Amazon bubble pack. This battery was what I might describe as an exit sign battery. This would not fit my quad, and as soon as I opened the bubble pack, I realized what it was and immediately went to return it only to find that this seller has a No Return Policy. Unable to determine if it was easily installed nor if it has longevity. Wish I could have been more help.Update: 7/20/2023 the battery no longer holds enough charge to turn over a 300cc generator engine.
